KARIMA Brown, ’n veteraan-joernalis wat tot onlangs nog op eNCA se aktualiteitsprogram, The Fix, te sien was, het haar stryd teen Covid-19 verloor. Brown (53) is vroeg in Februarie in die hospitaal opgeneem met komplikasies weens die virus. Luidens berigte was sy vir weke lank op ’n ventilator. Brown was ’n gesoute joernalis wat bekend was vir haar no-nonsense aanslag. Met dié aanslag het sy menigte politieke leiers tot verantwoording geroep. Sy het by verskeie mediahuise, waaronder die SABC, Independent Group, Primedia en eMedia, gewerk. eNCA het op hul Twitter account die nuus oor haar dood gebreek. My deepest condolences to Karima Brown's family following the news of her passing. She was courageous, bold and incredibly fearless. May her soul rest in peace. Ms Karima Brown’s passing is sudden and heartbreaking. She was a brilliant journalist and now broadcaster. Sending my deepest condolences to her family, her friends and colleagues. South African media has lost one of its loudest voice - I’ll miss our robust engagements. pic.twitter.com/kYXd7Ujz22 Still battling to wrap my mind around the news that Karima Brown is no more. This shocked me to the core. Heartfelt condolences to the family, friends and colleagues. Thank you for your fearless commitment to necessary conversations #KarimaBrown #RIPKarimaBrown pic.twitter.com/M2RaUHeYz3 I’m shattered to hear the news of Karima Brown’s passing. She fought hard for young talent in newsrooms. I’m one of those she gave platform to when many wouldn’t. I know she was fighting hard in hospital but ultimately the choice is never really ours.May her soul rest in peace ???? This is sad news indeed. I would like to extend my condolences to the family of Karima Brown and to her work colleagues. May her soul Rest In Peace ??. https://t.co/SDSls4HXkn 